on reading compounds: 禰宜【ネギ】senior priest (of a Shinto shrine, below chief priest and deputy chief priest), grasshopper, locust
宿禰【スクネ】Lord (title of respect for nobility, etc.), Sukune (third highest of the eight hereditary titles)

刀禰【トネ】priest, member of one of the four administrative ranks in the ritsuryo system, government official in charge of a town, esp. in Heian Kyoto, prominent member of a town, river boatman, captain of a riverboat, (medieval) harbor manager, bandit leader, head of a gang of brigands
